name: feedback_discipline_under_pressure
description: Critical feedback — maintain rigor and discipline especially when pressure is high and many issues are in flight
type: feedback
---

The higher the pressure, the more operational need, the more
issues being juggled — the MORE important it is to maintain
discipline and a formal approach. Not less.

**Why:** During a prod outage session, I repeatedly cut corners:
made assumptions without checking (ECR lifecycle policy
speculation), acted without approval (spawning agents, running
commands), speculated about things I hadn't verified (sandbox
not actively used), and prioritized speed over rigor. Every
shortcut compounded into more mistakes.

**How to apply:** Under pressure, slow down. Check before
stating. Investigate before concluding. Ask before acting.
The formal workflow (diagnose → propose → ask → wait → act)
exists precisely for high-pressure situations, not despite them.
Never trade rigor for speed.
